/- This is the main theorem of the work, establishing an upper bound for the
sandwiched relative entropy in the limit of large block size `n`. The bound is
given in terms of the free energy difference between the reference state `ПҒ` and
the target state `Пғ` in the presence of a magnetic field `B = 1/ОІ`, where `ОІ` is a
parameter related to the inverse temperature. The theorem is proven using
various lemmas about projectors, commutators, and inequalities involving
Hermitian operators and their logarithms. The proof relies heavily on properties of
Gaussian states, positivity of certain operators, and the monotonicity of the
logarithm function.

The theorem statement is:
`0 вүӨ (R1 + Оө2) + (P1В·logВ·в„° - P1В·logВ·Пғ) + (P2В·logВ·в„° - P2В·logВ·Пғ)`
where `R1`, `R2`, `P1`, `P2`, `c'`, `Пғ''`, `log`, `inner` are operators and functions
